The paper deals with managing historical data for large evolving information networks, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the design and architecture of a distributed graph database system, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents analytical models and experimental evaluations, which are common in the field of systems and information (cs.SI).
